The paper deals with algorithms for computing similarity measures between curves or temporal sequences, which are fundamental problems in various fields of computer science and computational biology. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The focus on dynamic programming algorithms and quadratic runtime also suggests a connection to cs.DP (Dynamic Programming), but this sub-category is less likely given the broader scope of the paper.
